# Database — use Postgres for local + Vercel (Neon free works well)
# Example Neon:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/neondb?sslmode=require"
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require"

# Auth.js — generate a long random string for production
AUTH_SECRET="generate-a-long-random-string"
# On Vercel, set to your deployment URL, e.g. https://hibernia-xxx.vercel.app
AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Outlook / Microsoft 365 SMTP — send dispatch PDFs
# Default host is smtp.office365.com (Microsoft 365 business)
# For personal outlook.com you may use: SMTP_HOST=smtp-mail.outlook.com
SMTP_HOST="smtp.office365.com"
SMTP_PORT="587"
SMTP_USER="briancasey@hiberniatrading.com"
SMTP_PASS="outlook-password-or-microsoft-app-password"
MAIL_FROM_NAME="Hibernia Dispatch"
#
# What Brian / IT need:
# 1. Confirm SMTP AUTH is allowed for this mailbox (Microsoft 365 admin center
#    sometimes disables it by default).
# 2. If MFA is on, create a Microsoft "App password" (or use an app password
#    policy your IT provides) and put THAT in SMTP_PASS — not his day-to-day
#    password if IT forbids it.
# 3. SMTP_USER must be the full email address.

# Google Sheets mirror (one-way: app → sheet)
#
# SETUP (once):
# 1. https://console.cloud.google.com → create/select a project
# 2. APIs & Services → Enable "Google Sheets API"
# 3. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → Service account
#    - Name e.g. hibernia-dispatch
#    - Grant no special project roles required for Sheets-only use
# 4. Open the service account → Keys → Add key → JSON → download the file
#    Save it somewhere safe OUTSIDE the git repo, e.g.
#    C:\Users\damia\OneDrive\Documents\Hibernia-secrets\google-service-account.json
# 5. Create a Google Sheet (or use an existing one). Rename a tab to "Loads"
#    (or leave blank — the app will create a "Loads" tab and write headers)
# 6. Share the spreadsheet with the service account EMAIL
#    (looks like: hibernia-dispatch@PROJECT.iam.gserviceaccount.com)
#    Permission: Editor
# 7. Copy the spreadsheet ID from the URL:
#    https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/THIS_PART_IS_THE_ID/edit
# 8. Fill the vars below and restart npm run dev
#
GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID="your-spreadsheet-id-from-url"
GOOGLE_SHEETS_TAB_NAME="Loads"
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="C:\\Users\\damia\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Hibernia-secrets\\google-service-account.json"
# Alternative to the file path (single-line JSON; use \\n inside private_key):
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}

# Optional: path override for rate sheet import
# RATES_XLSX_PATH="C:\\Users\\you\\Downloads\\Volume Freight Rates Calgary.xlsx"
